General Electric Co's RCA GlobalCommunications said it now offers RCA THRUFAX, a service thatdelivers telex messages to facsimile terminals.    No special equipment or extra cost is required to receivetelex messages, but the facsimile terminal must be registered -without charge - with RCA, the company said.    The company said through the service, every telex terminalin the world will be able to reach RCA-registered facsimileterminals in the U.S., of which there are approximately500,000. Reuter&#3;